Class Operator<OUT,O extends Operator<OUT,O>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flink.api.java.DataSet<OUT>
      • org.apache.flink.api.java.operators.Operator<OUT,O>
  • Type Parameters:
    OUT - The type of the data set produced by this operator.
    O - The type of the operator, so that we can return it.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DataSource, SingleInputOperator, TwoInputOperator

      • name

        public O name(String newName)
        Sets the name of this operator. This overrides the default name, which is either a generated description of the operation (such as for example "Aggregate(1:SUM, 2:MIN)") or the name the user-defined function or input/output format executed by the operator.
        Parameters:
        newName - The name for this operator.
        Returns:
        The operator with a new name.

      • setParallelism

        Parameters:
        dop - The degree of parallelism for this operator.
        Returns:
        The operator with set degree of parallelism.
